	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64118201"><p><div class="quote"><p>Or peel back one more onion layer to car dealerships: Tesla, Rivian, and other EV companies are selling directly to consumers, cutting them out. EVs also require little service compared with gas vehicles, a reality that has upset many dealers, who could lose their biggest source of profit.</p></div><p>I've viewed the Hybrid car as the incumbent manufacturers way of paying lip service to the environmental issues of ICE vehicles while keeping the dealerships happy.<br>More than happy; Electric + ICE = more complexity than just ICE and thus more potential for something breaking and/or needing servicing. The dealers wet dream.</p></div>
	</div>

