	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64118435"><p>Two years ago when my wife and I bought a Kia EV I'd have agreed with you; I was driving a Prius daily and she drove the Kia. Road trips did take some planning with the Kia, longest being about 300 miles one way.</p><p>When we got our Tesla to replace the Prius, my opinion changed.  The key factor was the supercharger network. Much faster than DC fast charging and far more reliable, it flipped my opinion on EV road tripping.</p><p>Tesla did the groundwork the right way; not only did it build the cars but it alap built out the infrastructure needed to keep them on the road.  That's the systems engineering approach and in my opinion was critical to Tesla's successful EV launch and production.</p></div>
	</div>

