	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64118475">Anyone who uses the percentage of emission free power on the local grid as the basis for EV emissions either doesn't know what they talking about or are being deliberately deceptive. The grid is not some giant pool of electricity, every time someone flips on a switch somewhere on the grid something has to  produce the increased power. There are exceptions, but there are very few places where there is excess emission free capacity to use. Instead it is usually burning more coal or more natural gas.The result</div>
