	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64118323">The problem with [insert non-BEV option here] is I have a BEV that I can charge for free at home from my solar panels and I have had for 4 years with zero problems.  Therefore other options all look like a step backwards to me, how do you compete with free?  Your point about expensive was true, 4 years ago when I brought my car, but they have now reached price parity with ICEV in my country, YMMV.  There are zero hydrogen or NH3 vehicles on the road here, matching the number of public fueling station for them.  I think BEVs have now reached about 20% of new sales here with supply, not price, being the main issue.
<br> <br>
There is no tech on the horizon that will dethrone BEVs. Hydrogen and NH3 are going nowhere without major investors and any would be investor who does market research is going to see once people have experienced living with a BEV they are not in a hurry to go back to the gas station model of fuel distribution and costs.</div>
	</div>

