	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64118347"><p>All vehicles have been zero emissions for 20 years?</p><p>Tire particulate contributes the most to smog?</p><p>Do you live in reality?</p><p>Here is the smog source contribution:</p><p>

<strong>Transportation (total): 53%</strong>
</p><ul>
<li>Vehicle Exhaust: ~45%
<ul>
<li>Gasoline vehicles</li><li>Diesel trucks</li><li>Other engine exhaust</li></ul></li><li>Tire and Brake Wear: ~3-5%
<ul>
<li>Rubber, metals, chemicals</li></ul></li><li>Gas Vapors: ~3-5%
<ul>
<li>Unburned volatile compounds</li></ul></li></ul><p>

<strong>Power Generation: 26%</strong>
</p><ul>
<li>Coal, Natural Gas, Oil</li></ul><p>

<strong>Industrial Processes: 11%</strong>
</p><ul>
<li>Chemical production</li><li>Petroleum refining</li><li>Cement, metals production</li></ul><p>

<strong>Fires: 6%</strong>
</p><ul>
<li>Wildfires</li><li>Agricultural burns</li><li>Prescribed burns</li></ul><p>

<strong>Oil and Gas Operations: 3%</strong>
</p><ul>
<li>Drilling, pipelines, production</li></ul><p>

<strong>Other Minor Sources: 1%</strong></p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64118347">
